{"type":"message","id":"04aa063e","parentId":"74142f05","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:28:35.533Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6yxkvwvoiw7r_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 3307\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/CFI-COMPRESSION-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1419\r\n[mutation proposed] research/CFI-COMPRESSION-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master afec453] pulse: 2026-03-24 122814\n 5 files changed, 194 insertions(+), 64 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 122814.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 122814.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 122814 - CFI analysis revealed 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI�0.7). This suggests frequency-based compression is heavily contaminated with metaprogramming artifacts rather than research trajectory signal.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"wild-sable","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 3307\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/CFI-COMPRESSION-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1419\r\n[mutation proposed] research/CFI-COMPRESSION-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master afec453] pulse: 2026-03-24 122814\n 5 files changed, 194 insertions(+), 64 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 122814.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 122814.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 122814 - CFI analysis revealed 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), while only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI�0.7). This suggests frequency-based compression is heavily contaminated with metaprogramming artifacts rather than research trajectory signal.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369715531}}
{"type":"message","id":"664f0f8e","parentId":"04aa063e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:28:35.535Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6yxkvwvoiw7r_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 122714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent activity:\r\n- Phase 0 and 1 are complete\r\n- CFI analysis is done - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment, CFI filtering, distinguishing constant format vs research trajectory, wiring to TemporalAttention backend, designing actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next step based on the CFI analysis is the CFI-weighted compression experiment. The current pulse script (pulse.ps1) likely uses frequency-based compression. The CFI analysis suggests that weighting by CFI would give better results than pure frequency.\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the current pulse script to understand how compression is currently done, and then propose a CFI-weighted variant.\r\n\r\nActually, I should first look at what files exist and understand the current compression mechanism before designing the experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions and the CFI findings, the logical next step is to design the CFI-weighted compression experiment. But first I need to examine how compression is currently implemented in the pulse script.\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that frequency-based compression loses 81.9% of causal signal. CFI weighting should preserve research trajectory content while filtering metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0). Need to examine current compression logic before designing the experiment.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nReview pulse.ps1 to understand current compression mechanism, then create experiment specification for CFI-weighted compression comparison.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-based compression for next-pulse prediction because:\r\n- **High CFI (>0.7)**: True causal anchors → preserve these (research trajectory)\r\n- **Low CFI (<0.3)**: Metaprogramming artifacts → can be removed safely\r\n- **Zero CFI**: Pure noise → remove entirely\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline (Current)\r\n- Frequency-based compression in pulse.ps1\r\n- All tokens with freq >= threshold are retained\r\n- No CFI weighting\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted\r\n- Retain tokens where: `freq >= threshold AND CFI > 0.3`\r\n- Remove tokens where: `CFI <= 0.3` (noise + artifacts)\r\n- Priority preserve: `CFI >= 0.7` (true causal anchors)\r\n\r\n### Success Metrics\r\n1. **Coherence score**: LLM evaluation of next-pulse context quality (1-10)\r\n2. **Prediction accuracy**: Does context enable accurate next-pulse prediction?\r\n3. **Compression ratio**: Tokens retained vs total\r\n4. **Signal preservation**: Mean CFI of retained tokens\r\n\r\n## Implementation Plan\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Extract Current Compression Logic\r\nFrom pulse.ps1, identify frequency threshold and retention mechanism.\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Create CFI-Weighted Variant\r\n```\r\nif (freq >= freq_threshold AND cfi > 0.3):\r\n    retain\r\nelif (cfi >= 0.7):\r\n    retain  # even if low frequency, high causal weight\r\nelse:\r\n    discard\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Run Parallel Experiments\r\n- Pulse with baseline compression → measure coherence\r\n- Pulse with CFI-weighted compression → measure coherence\r\n- Compare results over 10+ pulses\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Analysis\r\n- Which produces more coherent next-pulse context?\r\n- What's the tradeoff in compression ratio?\r\n- Does CFI filtering improve or hurt continuity?\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted should produce **better coherence with equivalent or better compression** because it removes noise while preserving true causal structure.\r\n\r\n## Next Action\r\nImplement CFI filtering in pulse.ps1 as step toward this experiment.\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:27:33\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369715533}}
